You can achieve that with `ViewChild` and the `AfterViewInit` hook:

- `ViewChild` let you select a child component from the parent
- `AfterViewInit` is triggered when the parent view (with all its children) is initialized. When this happens, we can get the refer the child component and invoke its public method `trackUser`

Here&#39;s the main code to do it
```
import { Component, ViewChild, AfterViewInit } from &#39;@angular/core&#39;;
import {HelloComponent} from &#39;./hello.component&#39;;

@Component({
  selector: &#39;my-app&#39;,
  template: `
    &lt;hello&gt;&lt;/hello&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;
      check the console, trackUser of helloComponent is called from the parent
    &lt;/p&gt;
  `,
})
export class AppComponent implements AfterViewInit  {
  name = &#39;Angular&#39;;

  @ViewChild(HelloComponent) helloComp: HelloComponent;

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    this.helloComp.trackUser();
  }

  
}

```

